author: Andrew Mark Miller
title: Paul Krugman Is Still Blaming Everyone Else For Hillary’s Loss And It Backfired INSTANTLY
text:
Remember when Paul Krugman’s opinion carried a lot of water? 
Yeah, me neither. 
We can’t even really call him an economist anymore. 
He gave up on the idea of being unbiased a long time ago. 
It looks like he still just can’t get over the fact that Hillary lost and he’s still pointing fingers about it. I try not to look back, but every once in a while: we could have had a smart, sane president, but media preferred to hype email non-scandal 
— Paul Krugman (@paulkrugman) February 13, 2017 
Krugman doesn’t even think it was a scandal? 
I get that liberals don’t think compromising national security is a big deal but to not even acknowledge that Hillary’s emails were a scandal is pretty detached. 
Here are the best responses on Twitter. He still thinks this is why she lost. https://t.co/vPZipFG3ug
